  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Telecommunications Sector Coordination and Services to enable scale-up of life saving humanitarian assistance to the most vulnerable populations.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WFP will provide emergency telecommunications and data communication services to the humanitarian community in the targeted areas in order to allow relief workers to operate and provide immediate lifesaving assistance to populations affected by the crisis. The Emergency Telecommunications Sector (ETS) will provide security telecommunications and internet access at the humanitarian hubs based on current planning by the Humanitarian Hubs Task Force in priority geographic locations such as Dambosa and Damasak to enable more humanitarians to have continuous presence in order to deliver a more effective humanitarian response.</narrative>
  </description>
